# Pulsys / pulsys Docker build context — keep images fast and small.
#
# The compose Dockerfile only needs:
#   go.mod, go.sum, cmd/, internal/          (Go binaries)
#   admin-ui/package*.json, admin-ui/src/…   (static admin export)
#   docker/                                   (nginx + init scripts + Keycloak import)
#
# Everything else stays out of `COPY . .` and shrinks context transfer
# (tmp/ alone is multi-GB on dev machines).

# --- VCS, CI, editor scratch ---
.git
.gitignore
.github
.cursor
.DS_Store
.idea
.vscode

# --- Unrelated repo areas (not compiled into Pulsys images) ---
website
infra
docs
scripts
# Phase 4.5: re-include the security-tests entrypoint so
# Dockerfile.security-tests can COPY it.  Everything else
# under scripts/ stays excluded.
!scripts/security-tests-entrypoint.sh
compose.yaml
Dockerfile.test
LICENSE
README.md

# --- Bench / cache / local run artifacts ---
tmp
cache
bin
hfhub.test
*.test
*.prof
*.pb.gz
*.cover
coverage.out

# --- Node deps (never copied into Go images) ---
node_modules

# --- Admin UI: source only; deps and build output come from npm ci/build ---
admin-ui/node_modules
admin-ui/.next
admin-ui/out
admin-ui/.env*
admin-ui/README.md

# --- Archives and bulky downloads ---
**/*.tar.gz
**/*.zip
